title: For Sale:  New Version of the Army Duffel Bag
postcontent: For sale is a US Army issue duffel bag. These have a full-length double zipper that allows one to access the whole bag. For anyone who has used an Army duffel, there are times where what you need is at the bottom of the duffel, and essentially one has to dump the whole duffel to be able to get at it. These duffels don't have that problem, you can unzip the bag to see what is in it from top to bottom. However, the hasp where you can put a lock to prevent others from getting into the bag is retained and the zips can be situated so that they are under the hasp when closed. Also, these duffels have backpack straps, just like the old ones, so that the bag can be carried on the back. There are also handles on both ends for pulling the bag in and out of storage and a handle on the top for carrying with one hand. On one side of the bag there is a clear document holder that can be used to slip in either the name of the owner, or perhaps the contents of the bag. Essentially one can put whatever one wants in the document holder, presumably to idenfity the owner or contents of the bag.   This bag is new, but may show some storage marks from being in a tote. It originated with the US government, and is the same bag that they sell at AAFES clothing and sales for $40. I have more pictures if needed.
